            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Hd1e108">Rubrica 17</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De iudiciali vindicta</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>
      ¶ De iudiciali mundicia. Rubrica. 17
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="86"/><ref>MOises in deuteronomio
      <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>c. 24</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e125">Non occiden
        <lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>tur patres pro filiis: nec filii pro pa
        <lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>tribus: sed vnusquisque pro suo pec <!--145.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="59-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1" break="no"/>cato moriatur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e142">
               <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>
              ¶ <ref>Salomon in prouer. c. 20.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e146">Dissipat impios
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>rex sapiens.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e153"> /
               <ref>Idem in eccl. c. 8.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e155">Quia non pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="4" break="no"/>fertur cito contra malos sententia absque vllo ti
        <lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>more filii hominum perpetrant mala.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e163">
               <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>
             ¶ <ref>Hieremias propheta li. prophetarum. c. 31.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e167">Omnis
        <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>homo qui comederit vuam: acerbam et dentes
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>ei obstupescent.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e175">
               <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>
             ¶ <ref>Ezechiel propheta. c. 18.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e179">Ezechiel ait: Factus
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>est sermo domini ad me dicens: Fili hominis quid
        <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>est quod inter vos parabolam vertitis in prouerbium
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>istud inter israhel dicentes: Patres nostri comederunt
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>vuam acerbam: et dentes filiorum obstupescunt.
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>Anima que peccauerit ipsa morietur: filius non
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>portabit iniquitatem patris: et pater non porta
        <lb ed="#V" n="16" break="no"/>bit iniquitatem filii. Iustitia iusti super eum erit
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>et impietas impii erit super eum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e200">
               <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>
             ¶ <ref>Aristoteles retho. li. i. c. 19</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e204">Differunt pu
        <lb ed="#V" n="19" break="no"/>nitio et castigatio. Castigatio quidem enim pa
        <lb ed="#V" n="20" break="no"/>tientis gratia est. Punitio autem facientis vt sa
        <lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>tietur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e214"> /
               <ref>Lib. 3. et fi. c. 12.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e216">Uindicta nocu
        <lb ed="#V" n="22" break="no"/>mentum quoddam iustum est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e222"> /
               <ref>Idem pollitico
        <lb ed="#V" n="23" break="no"/>rum li. 7. c. 10.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e224">Punitiones a virtute quidem sunt</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e231">
               <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>
             ¶ <ref><sic>Pilon</sic> vel philemodo li. sapiente. c. 11.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e235">Per qua
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>peccat quis per hec et torquetur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e241">
               <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>
             ¶ <ref>Tullius rethoricorum artis veteris li. 11. c. 5</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e245">Nihil est indignius quam eum qui culpa caret
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>supplitio non carere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e253">
               <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>
             ¶ <ref>Quintilianus declamationum. 13 declam.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e257">Facinus est o iudices euadere nocentes.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e263">
               <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>
             ¶ <ref>Seneca tragediarum in hercule furente. c. 11
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>et fi.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e267">Sepe vindicta obfuit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e273"> /
               <ref>Idem in prouerb.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e275">Nunquam scelus scelere iudicandum est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e281">
               <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
             ¶ <ref>Lex diges. ti. de operis noui nunci. li. de pu
        <lb ed="#V" n="35" break="no"/>pillo. §. si plurium.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e285">Non debet nocere factum alte
        <lb ed="#V" n="36" break="no"/>rius ei qui nihil fecit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e294"> /
               <ref>Ti. de fideiussoribus
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>l. si a reo. §. fi.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e296">Penas ob male ficia solui ma
        <lb ed="#V" n="38" break="no"/>gna ratio suadet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e302"> / 
               <ref>Ti. de reg. iur. l. infrascri
        <lb ed="#V" n="39" break="no"/>pta.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e304">Non debet alteri per alterum iniqua con
        <lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>ditio inferri.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e308"> 
             ¶ <ref>Lex codi. ti. de epis. et cleri.
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>l. presbyteri:</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e310">Multomagis pena sunt digni
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>quibus cum plurimum honoris est delatum: oc
        <lb ed="#V" n="43" break="no"/>culto inueniuntur in crimine.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e320"> /
               <ref>Ti. de iudeis.
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>l. nemo.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e322">Iccirco iudiciorum vigor iurisque pub
        <lb ed="#V" n="45" break="no"/>lici tutela videtur in medio constituta ne quisquam <!--145.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>sibiipsi permittere valeat vltionem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e339"> /
               <ref>Ti. de pe
        <lb ed="#V" n="47" break="no"/>nis. l. si operis:</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e341">Non remitti penam facile publi
        <lb ed="#V" n="48" break="no"/>ce interest: ne ad maleficia quisquam temere pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>filiat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e349">
               <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>
             ¶ <ref><sic>Beotius</sic> de consolatione lib. 4. c. 7.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e351">Puniri
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>improbos iustum est: impunitos elabi etiam
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>iniquum esse manifestum est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e358">
               <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>
             ¶ <ref>Cassiodorus epistolarum li. i. e. 4.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e362">Excessus tunc
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>sunt in formidine quando creduntur iudicibus dis
        <lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>plicere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e370"> /
               <ref>Li. 4. e. 35.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e372">Esset cunctis fallendi
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>studium si fraus subuecticium lucraretur effectum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e379">
               <lb ed="#V" n="57"/> /
               <ref>49. e.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e383">Necesse est vindicte subiaceat qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>prauis moribus obsecundat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e389"> /
               <ref>Libro. 5. e. 14</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e391">Iustitie ratio persuadet excedentes reprimere
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>vt ad cunctos possit quietis suauitas perueni
        <lb ed="#V" n="61" break="no"/>re.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e401"> /
               <ref>Libro. 9. e. 2.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e403">Uix audet quisquem in il
        <lb ed="#V" n="62" break="no"/>los excedere: in quibus culpas non potest inue
        <lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>nire.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e411"> /
               <ref>Lib. 9. e. 22.</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e413">Indiscreti hominum mo
        <lb ed="#V" n="64" break="no"/>res confusique vagarentur si aut culpa formidinem
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>aut virtus praemia non haberet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-d1e421">
               <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>
             ¶ <ref>Auctor li. qui dicitur pamphilus. c. 22</ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44894-Qd1e425">Pe
        <lb ed="#V" n="67" break="no"/>nas sepe luit quas homo non meruit.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
